==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cajuput
<hw>Caj"u*put</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Of Malayan origin;
<ets>k⟦amac⟧yu</ets> tree + <ets>p⟦umac⟧tih</ets> white.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A highly stimulating volatile inflammable oil,
distilled from the leaves of an East Indian tree (<spn>Melaleuca
cajuputi</spn>, etc.) It is greenish in color and has a camphoraceous
odor and pungent taste.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cajuputene</ent>⟦br⟧
